---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Ace Combat Zero: The Belkan War Pre-order Bonus Explained"
  description="Ace Combat 8 eligible preorders include an Ace Combat Zero: The Belkan War port. Compare platform versions, languages and offer caveats."
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Ace Combat Zero Bonus' }]} />
  <article class="container article">
    <span class="eyebrow">For returning series fans</span>
    <h1>The Ace Combat Zero Bonus</h1>

    <p class="direct-answer" data-concrete-answer>
      Eligible ACE COMBAT 8 preorders include a port of <strong>ACE COMBAT ZERO: THE BELKAN
      WAR</strong> for the purchased platform. PlayStation and Steam explicitly identify their
      respective versions; verify the current regional storefront terms before payment.
    </p>

    <h2>Why this bonus matters</h2>
    <p>
      Ace Combat Zero originally released in 2006 and is widely regarded as one of the
      defining entries in the franchise, particularly for introducing the <strong>Ace Style
      gauge</strong> — the same system mechanic returning in Wings of Theve, which makes this
      bonus feel less like a random freebie and more like a deliberate callback ahead of the
      new game reusing that same identity system.
    </p>

    <h2>What you get, by platform</h2>
    <table class="dossier-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Platform</th><th>Version included</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>PS5</td><td>Ace Combat Zero: The Belkan War (PS5 version)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>PC (Steam)</td><td>Ace Combat Zero: The Belkan War (Steam version)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Xbox Series X|S</td><td>Check the current regional Xbox offer listing</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p style="font-size:0.85rem;">
      Supported languages for the Belkan War port: Japanese, English, French, Italian, German,
      and Spanish. Note that this may not match Wings of Theve's own language support.
    </p>

    <div class="card callout">
      <p class="mono eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Also included with every pre-order</p>
      <p style="margin:0;">
        The playable <strong>F-14A</strong> aircraft, available from day one — see our
        <a href="/aircraft/f-14a">F-14A aircraft page</a> for unlock details.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedLinks items={[
    { href: '/preorder-bonuses', label: 'All Preorder Bonuses', desc: 'See the F-14A offer and timing caveats in one place.' },
    { href: '/languages/ace-combat-zero', label: 'Bonus Language Guide', desc: 'Check the published six-language Steam list.' },
    { href: '/editions', label: 'Editions Compared', desc: 'See exactly which editions include this bonus and what else you get.' },
    { href: '/ace-style-system', label: 'Ace Style System', desc: 'The mechanic Ace Combat Zero introduced, now returning in Wings of Theve.' },
  ]} />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article {
    padding: 56px 0 80px;
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .article p, .article li { font-size: 0.98rem; }
  .callout { margin: 28px 0; }
  .direct-answer { font-size: 1.08rem !important; border-left: 3px solid var(--hud-amber); padding-left: 18px; }
</style>
